post_text: Principal Hiltner read the book, "Sulwe" by Lupita Nyong'O to Mrs. Potratz's second-grade class. The book is great for teaching young ones that beauty comes from the inside-out and not the other way around. It also shows the beauty of all shades of skin color and it's importance in our world. One student said, "we are all uniquely beautiful!" Such great words of wisdom from seven-year-olds!

post_text:
First Day of School 2020.
We are OK.
Kids are the most amazing human beings - amazingly resilient! I watched as our students wore masks, socially distanced and washed hands! I watched parents drop their children off with hugs (and some tears) as they left them in our care. I watched our incredible staff show patience and love to all who needed it! Watching them reminds me that if our kids are ok, all else falls into place...and the little ones will lead us! ‚ô•Ô∏è Our first day is off to a great start in Manvel!
-Principal Hiltner

PS: Thanks to Cheryl St Yves McGillis and Montanna McGillis for the fun balloon arch they made in the entryway for the first day! üéâ

PLEASE stop! We are sharing way too much about schools opening next year and what they will look like. From every tired virtual teacher and exhausted homeschool parent ‚ÄúWe can‚Äôt take it‚Äù. Please stop.

üò±Do we need to fear next school year? NO. We need summertime joy.
üòîDo we need to have anxiety on our social media about things that have not even been determined? NO. We need to focus on all of our success so far.

We control social media sharing and what comes up on our feeds. We need to take back the power of this thing! Spread love, positivity, and grace- NOT fear. Don‚Äôt get sucked in.

post_text: The 2019-2020 school year will be one we will never forget because of the Coronavirus and Distance Learning. However, we also had 6 months of wonderful learning and memories that were overshadowed by the pandemic. Enjoy this small nugget of memories from MPS this year. It was a great year of learning ~ not only learning academics but learning HOPE, RESILIENCE, and life lessons that we would not have known without living through the pandemic. Although the school is part of the Manvel Community, the Manvel Community is DEFINITELY part of our school! We are thankful for the privilege of working with you and your children this year. Have a safe & healthy summer! ~ Mrs. Hiltner

Governor Burgum got a bit emotional during his press conference today when talking about how educators and families have really stepped up and made distance learning a reality throughout the state. North Dakota has led the nation in our K-12 response to this crisis and we should all feel very proud of ourselves and each other! Way to go NoDak parents, students, teachers, paras, nutrition staff, administrators, counselors, tech support, and state leadership!!
That being said, the Governor confirmed that the remainder of this school year will be completed via distance learning. If you have questions, please contact your school or district directly.
#NDSmart

ND Department of Public Instruction
April 1 at 1:00 PM ¬∑

An update on the progress of North Dakota's school distance learning plans. 171 districts had to submit plans. As of early Monday afternoon, Superintendent Kirsten Baesler and Governor Doug Burgum's office have approved all 171. A number of plans required back-and-forth work with the review teams at ND Department of Public Instruction and the governor's office, but the goal of everyone having an approved distance learning plan has been reached. Congratulations to our North Dakota educators, who took on a Herculean task and did it with aplomb!
